div.div:
- Save recorded interactions and last transform of current Player class and name of Player (Player class is attached to a certain GameObject (agent))
- Remove EventListener from all ability actions of old Player
- Get transform of current player and instantiate new Player (with CharacterData from List) at this position based on the selection from the UI element
- Camera focusses on new Player and add EventListener to PlayerController to listen to Ability events ("CreateInteraction") (event contains performed Interaction)
- Old Player is removed from the scene and add an old player with new Player class at saved transform position
- Current player in PlayerController refers to Player 2

div.div: When the first splitting happens, the current game time is saved to a variable (level time). From there on the level time ressembles the current real time. It constantly moves forward and all recorded interactions are executed based on the respective time stamp saved for each interaction. The level time is set back to the different splitting moments when merging backwards.

div.font:
TimeController (or new TimelineController) creates a NodeTree of Timelines. At the start of the game, the rootTimeline is created.
This Timeline stores split Timelines as their Children. When split, a new AlternateTimeline gets created, which stores a reference to the selected character and the splitTimeStamp.
A state of the interactable GameObjects in the scene also has to be stored. When merged (or collapsed), the recorded data during that time is stored in currentTimeline.playerSaveData.
The currentTimeline is set to the previous (current = current.getParent()) node. The gameTime is set to the splitTimestamp of the current Timeline. The gameObjects reset to the stored State and the recorded inputs start playing on the old current character.
This NodeTree can also be used to represent the timeGrap, since every AlternateTimeline has a timeStamp.
